snippet.textDisplay: Everyone casually saying how they use adblock yet that means the channels they like aren't getting any revenue. I want to support the channels I like and if they make money through ads that's fine with me. However, the recent upsurge in ads had now made me consider an adblocker. Using YouTube is becoming intolerable and I have given up even trying to watch several videos due to ads. I'm sure Google has a strategy that's something like push things beyond breaking point and then scale back to find the sweet spot but it has been like this for months and it's getting worse. Double ads, double mid-video ads are taking the piss and I won't accept it. And YouTube Premium isn't an option, Google already knows everything about us and it's worth trillions, I'm not giving them my money as a reward for their scummy tactics.
